      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (NIH, pressure rise, velocity field) must be directly traceable to the clinical endpoint (chronic hemolysis below 0.01 mg/100 mL).",
      "rationale": "NIH is the regulatory QoI per FDA guidance on VAD hemolysis. Pressure rise and velocity field are mechanistically linked to shear stress accumulation driving NIH. Traceability matrix from clinical endpoint to each validation QoI documented in credibility plan v3.1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
